  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently, the `JaxbMessageBodyWriter` from `quarkus-resteasy-reactive-jaxb-common` uses `javax.xml.bind.JAXB.marshal()` to marshal objects to XML. There is no way to customize the marshaller, apart from forking the whole extension and replacing `JaxbMessageBodyWriter` all together.\r\n\r\nSo if for example I'd need to change the `Marshaller.JAXB_FORMATTED_OUTPUT` property, I have no easy way of doing so.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nI see a couple of ways how this could be done, each with its own pros and cons:\r\n\r\n* provide settings for properties and pass them via `javax.xml.bind.Marshaller.setProperts(String, Object)`\r\n* some SPI/Injection based approach would allow to provide own implementations of the `javax.xml.bind.Marshaller`, which could offer more flexibility then a simple `setProperty` based approach, but most probably at the cost of complexity\r\n* an annotation based approach (e.g. via `org.jboss.resteasy.spi.DecoratorProcessor`) would have the benefit of being able to even provide different marshallers for the various resources, but may add even more complexity\r\n* make it easier to extend and replace the default `JaxbMessageBodyWriter` implementation, e.g. by introducing a `protected Marshaller createMarshaller(JaxbContext context)` or `protected void marshal(Object, OutputStream)`, and a setting to replace the default `JaxbMessageBodyWriter` by any class extending it",
